---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AudienceSection from '../components/AudienceSection.astro';
import { AUDIENCE } from '../lib/audience';
import { SITE } from '../lib/site';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="HotPick Lab serves US shoppers and short-form creators with independent buying briefs on trending products — who to buy, who to skip, and why."
  keywords={['about hotpick lab', 'buying briefs', 'worth it guides', 'trending product research']}
>
  <article class="prose about-page">
    <h1>About {SITE.name}</h1>
    <p class="about-lead">{AUDIENCE.mission}</p>

    <h2>What we publish</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE.name} is an independent research site for the <strong>US market</strong>. We publish
      <strong>buying briefs</strong> — structured guides on products spiking in search and social:
      viral Amazon finds, AI tools for creators, gaming accessories, and seasonal deals.
    </p>
    <p>
      Each brief answers the same decision questions: <strong>who should buy</strong>,
      <strong>who should skip</strong>, common pitfalls, a short compared pick list, and a clear
      verdict. We also ship <strong>free browser tools</strong> for deal math, video sizing, and
      session timing.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="/methodology">Read our research methodology →</a>
    </p>

    <AudienceSection showNotFor={true} compact={true} />

    <h2 id="how-we-pick">How we choose topics</h2>
    <p>
      Every week we scan US-market signals — rising searches, viral products, launch cycles, and
      seasonal retail moments — then ask:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Is purchase intent real, or is the trend already fading?</li>
      <li>Can we deliver a useful buy / skip / wait answer on one page?</li>
      <li>Would we honestly tell some readers not to buy?</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      If we cannot add clarity, we do not publish. Briefs are revised when prices, products, or
      hype shift — not left with outdated picks.
    </p>

    <h2>Transparency</h2>
    <p>
      We may earn affiliate commissions when you buy through our links. That never changes our
      skip lists or verdicts — we make nothing when you decide not to buy.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="/disclosure">Affiliate disclosure →</a> ·
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy policy →</a>
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions, corrections, or product updates? Email
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-lead {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #d9e2ff;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .about-page :global(.audience) {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }
</style>
